Amazon has unveiled a new Fire TV Cube. The “all-new” Fire TV Cube is the fastest and most powerful Fire TV device to date and features support for 4K content, HDR10+, and Dolby Vision. Amazon said the device will start shipping on 10 October and is available to order for $119.99. The Fire TV Cube also comes with Alexa built in, so users can use their voice to control their viewing and other devices linked to the Cube. Connectivity is taken care of via its Ethernet port or 802.11ac Wi-Fi, while the Cube connects to your display via HDMI. On the software side, streaming platforms Netflix, YouTube, Prime Video, Showtime, and more are supported.